						<summary>

						<p>In the main <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Rāmachandra-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p>1616 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in Rākshasa, Paṅguṉi. 4, which will correspond to 1616 A.D., February-March. This records the gift of 6 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> per month and 150 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land to Mārgasahāya Paṇḍitar, a physician, by Śōṇādri Ayyaṉ, the agent of Raghunātha Nāyakar, Tirumalai-Ayyaṅgār, the <hi rend="italic">Śrīkāryam</hi> officer of the Rāmachandraperumāḷ temple and <hi rend="italic">the Śrībhaṇḍārattār.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
